This morning when my kids were eating breakfast my son asked,
&ldquo;Mom, what happened to your flower?&rdquo; I looked on the deck and it was gone. I asked my hubby if he moved it and he said,&quot; No, but last night when I was sitting out at the dining room table, I did hear a  crash outside when the wind blew.&quot;
My kids went out to investigate this morning and it seems my poor flower decided to take her life with a fateful jump off of our deck, rather than to continue to suffer under my care.
